She nodded. "Of course." She would enjoy Hevn's demise if it came to that. 

"Other than Sideays & Hevn... I don't suspect anyone else of such problems. 
Scourge, I can trust." she smirked at the thought of him. In his new form, the 
wolf humanoid/beast dragon. 

Waiting for all this to get over with. She actually, hoped for a little more 
time to be near Hydras. It was sad that all these years, all these millenia, 
she rarely had such an opportunity. & now that she had a great opportunity, it 
was still a rarity to be with him. She wondered how much of Hydras, what parts 
of Megatron & what parts of Galvatron had the actual feelings for her. Was it 
something recent? Was it something that stayed hidden for a long time. 

Pushing it all aside, Hydras was right, duty first... pleasure later.  


--part1_1ac.16669987.2c200002_boundary
